# text = Towards the middle of the day, after having, from time to time, for the sake of resting herself, travelled, for three or four sous a league, in what was then known as the _Petites Voitures des Environs de Paris_, the “little suburban coach service,” Fantine found herself at Montfermeil, in the alley Boulanger.
